## Radio X (United Kingdom)

**Radio X** is a [national radio station](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_radio_station) in the [United Kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom). It broadcasts on FM, [DAB](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_Audio_Broadcasting), and [online](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Online_radio). The station is owned by [Global](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_(company)), which also owns [Capital](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_(radio_station)), [Heart](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heart_(radio_station)), [LBC](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LBC), and [Classic FM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Classic_FM).

### History

Radio X was launched on 29 September 1992 as **Xfm** by [Capital Radio plc](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_Radio_plc). The station was conceived as an alternative to the mainstream [pop music](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pop_music) stations, focusing on [indie rock](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indie_rock), [alternative rock](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alternative_rock), and [Britpop](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Britpop). The first song played on Xfm was "Set You Free" by [OMD](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orchestral_Manoeuvres_in_the_Dark).

In its early years, Xfm struggled to find an audience, but it gradually built a loyal following among music fans who were looking for something different. The station was known for its eclectic playlist, its support for new and emerging artists, and its often-irreverent on-air presenters.

In 2000, Xfm was acquired by [Global Radio](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Radio), which rebranded the station as Radio X in 2015. The rebranding was intended to signal a shift in the station's music policy, with a greater emphasis on [rock music](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rock_music) and less on [indie](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indie_music).

### Programming

Radio X broadcasts a mix of music, news, and [talk shows](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Talk_radio). The station's music policy focuses on [rock music](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rock_music) from the 1990s to the present day, with a particular emphasis on [indie rock](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indie_rock), [alternative rock](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alternative_rock), and [classic rock](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Classic_rock). The station also plays some [electronic music](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electronic_music) and [hip hop](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hip_hop_music).

Radio X is known for its distinctive on-air presenters, who are often known for their wit, [irreverence](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Irreverence), and [deadpan humour](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deadpan). The station's most popular shows include:

*   **The Chris Moyles Show:** A [breakfast show](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breakfast_show) hosted by [Chris Moyles](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chris_Moyles), who is known for his [outspoken](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Outspoken) and [controversial](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Controversial) style.
*   **The Evening Show with Gordon Smart:** A late-night music and chat show hosted by [Gordon Smart](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gordon_Smart), who is known for his [dry wit](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dry_wit) and his ability to get guests to open up.
*   **The John Kennedy Show:** A specialist music show hosted by [John Kennedy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Kennedy_(radio_DJ)), who is known for his deep knowledge of [independent music](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Independent_music).

### Broadcasting

Radio X broadcasts on FM in [London](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London) and [Manchester](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manchester), and on DAB across the UK. The station also streams live online via its website and app.

### Criticism

Radio X has been criticized by some for its perceived shift in music policy since its rebranding from Xfm. Some listeners have argued that the station has become too mainstream and has lost touch with its [indie roots](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indie_music). Others have praised the station for its more diverse music offering and its continued support for [new artists](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emerging_artist).

